---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Performance First: Faster Web Apps | Balaji Blogs" description="Strategies and best practices for optimizing web performance and reducing latency.">
  <article class="animate-in">
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>Performance First: Faster Web Apps</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">Published on April 15, 2026 &bull; 4 min read</div>
    </header>

    <div class="article-content">
      <p>In modern web development, speed is a feature. Users expect pages to load near-instantaneously, and search engines heavily penalize sluggish performance metrics like First Contentful Paint (FCP) and Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS).</p>

      <h2>Asset Optimization</h2>
      <p>The simplest wins usually lie in resource management. Serving modern image formats like WebP or AVIF, optimizing heavy SVGs, and avoiding massive font payloads can shave whole seconds off a page's loading time.</p>

      <h2>Progressive Enhancement</h2>
      <p>When handling interactive JavaScript, employing server-side rendering (SSR) or static site generation (SSG) alongside progressive enhancement ensures that vital HTML and CSS are delivered immediately. Heavy client-side logic can hydrate asynchronously later.</p>

      <p>Prioritizing performance is no longer an afterthought; it needs to be baked into your architecture from day one if you want to deliver experiences that retain and convert users.</p>
    </div>

    <a href="/blog" class="back-link">&larr; Back to all articles</a>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .article-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .article-meta {
    color: var(--muted-text);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .article-content {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 3rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--muted-text);
  }

  .article-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .article-content h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-color);
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    color: var(--muted-text);
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent-color);
  }
</style>
